The function f(x) has a vertical asymptote at x = a if

\begin{align*}\lim_{x \rightarrow a^{+}} f(x) = \infty\,\,\text{or}\,-\infty, \quad \text{and/or}\quad \lim_{x \rightarrow a^{-}} f(x) = \infty\,\,\text{or}\,-\infty.\end{align*}

The function f(x) has a horizontal asymptote at y = b if

\begin{align*}\lim_{x \rightarrow +\infty} f(x) = b \quad \text{and/or} \quad \lim_{x \rightarrow -\infty} f(x) = b.\end{align*}
